        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1955-05-11T14:04:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1955-05-11T14:04:00-05:00" n="94"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d94">
                <head>94. Telegram From the <gloss type="from">Department of State</gloss> to the
                        <gloss type="to">Embassy in Egypt</gloss>
                    <note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d94fn1">Source: Department of State, Central
                        Files, 684A.86/5–1155. Top Secret; Alpha; Limited Distribution. Drafted by
                            <persName corresp="#p_RFH1">Russell</persName>; cleared with <persName
                            corresp="#p_JJD1">Jernegan</persName> and <persName corresp="#p_MRD1"
                            >Murphy</persName>; approved by <persName corresp="#p_RFH1"
                            >Russell</persName>; and initialed for <persName corresp="#p_HHJ1"
                            >Hoover</persName> by <persName corresp="#p_MRD1"
                        >Murphy</persName>.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>,<date calendar="gregorian" when="1955-05-11T14:04:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 11, 1955—2:04 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1960. For Ambassador only. For your personal information Secretary recently
                    discussed Alpha project with President,<note n="2" xml:id="d94fn2">See <ref
                            target="#d91fn2">footnote 2, Document 91</ref>.</note> stating time
                    appeared to have arrived for talk with <persName corresp="#p_NNNGA1"
                        >Nasser</persName>, that Alpha contemplated US–<gloss target="#t_UK1"
                        >UK</gloss> guarantee borders between Israel and neighboring Arab states and
                    also involved rather heavy financial implications. President indicated he
                    thought it in order for you speak to <persName corresp="#p_NNNGA1"
                        >Nasser</persName> on assumption any references to border guarantee or
                    additional financial assistance would be on purely exploratory basis and would
                    avoid any commitment US at this stage.</p>
                <p>Following Secretary’s return from Europe it is planned discuss Alpha proposals
                    with other interested Department heads and possibly three or four Congressional
                    leaders. Definiteness US undertaking give border guarantee and additional
                    economic and military aid will depend on results these discussions as well as of
                    course on <persName corresp="#p_NNNGA1">Nasser</persName>’s initial reactions
                    exploratory talks.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_HHJ1">
                            <hi rend="strong">Hoover</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
